==Turkish==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|tr|ota|یاورو|tr=yavru}}, {{der|tr|trk-pro|*yabrï}}.<ref>{{R:tut-pro:SDM|*jabrɨ|url=https://starling.rinet.ru/cgi-bin/response.cgi?single=1&basename=%2fdata%2falt%2fturcet&text_number=+947&root=config}}</ref> Cognate with {{cog|cv|ҫӑвӑр}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|tr|[javˈɾu]}}
* {{hyphenation|tr|yav|ru}}
===Noun===
{{tr-noun|yu|lar}}
# [[baby]] {{gloss|young animal}}
#: ''Kedimiz Mırnav, o sene dört '''yavru''' yavrulamıştı.''
#:: ''Our cat Mırnav gave birth to four kittens that year.'' {{gloss|Here, the baby animals are kittens.}}
# {{lb|tr|figurative}} A child
#: ''Hiç bir anne '''yavrusunu''' ateşe atar mı?''
#:: ''Would a mother ever throw her '''child''' to the fire?''
# {{lb|tr|figurative}} [[baby]] {{gloss|used to refer to an attractive person, most often female}}
#: ''Gel buraya güzelim, yavruların '''yavrusu'''!''
#:: ''Come here my beauty, [sexy] '''baby'''!''
